That said, I was a little surprised that temperatures weren‚Äôt taken at the start of class. <user>108746824392643840601< /user><name>John<//name>< date>
1613794033435</date>
< Rating>
1</Rating>
< review>
There are quite a few Thai restaurants in the south bay, and I've tried at least a dozen of them. So ignore the 5, 4, 3 star reviews.  I'll start with - SLOW DELIVERY! Took an hour. I'm only 6-7 miles away. Portions - SMALLEST I've had from any Thai restaurant. Usually order entrees for family of 3 and we were still hungry. Didn't even finish because food tasted HORRIBLE.. Pad see ew -  broccoli had a sour, strange taste, definitely not fresh, fried tofu was chewy (previously frozen?), noodles were dry. Green curry - super WATERY, not creamy like coconut milk. Fried rice w/shrimp - NOTHING to write home about. Cross this place off your list. I AM!</review>

< Text>
I loved the atmosphere of this place! But I ordered 2 805 draft beers and it was $15.50!! I was afraid to order food after that. There were great sandwiches on the menu, giant soft pretzels ( 7 bucks) smoothies, all sorts of goodies but my wallet was feeling skinny that day.< /Text>
< pictures>
[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNyMgfUntwfmOpJzCU6VnDr7zJE-yVUSiz1wUFn=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNk-DvZJ0yegbyowAKS-2QrxTO8nD7UsNBV5jLP=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]< /pictures>

< Text>
I love that The Beach has fresh and healthy options... especially thankful for the vegan options! I always seem to crave it when they're closed, but now and then, I catch them during business hours. Last time, I got a sandwich with hummus, cucumbers, sprouts, tomatoes. The bread was fresh and delicious. We also enjoyed a side of sliced vegetables with hummus and a Dole Whip to drink. It was more than I could eat in one meal, so I enjoyed some of it later.
I love to eat on the patio outside, enjoy the music, and someday, I'll get there for a live music performance (which they host regularly). Once, I watched a launch from the patio, great view and a comfortable seat!
One wish would be to offer vegan options for substitutes in the smoothies. Honey is a no go for me. I got a berry smoothie once but I was disappointed with no yogurt option and no sweetener... I got only berries, ice, and water :( but I know that it is only a matter of time and availability.
Thank you to the owner and employees for providing a much needed haven.</Text>

<time>1506717267370<//time><resp>None</resp>< Rate>
5</Rate>
<user_id>110383005080457158829<//user_id><username>Keith Feickert<//username>< Review>
The Beach has great ambience, lilies adorn the tables and provide a tropical scent along with the beach/surf memorabilia. The smoothies are very good, I had the peanut butter banana smoothie and it was delicious! The wood fire pizzas take some time to make however, so if you're in a lunch rush, it might be better to get a sandwich or soup here instead. The pizzas are well worth the wait though. It's hard to beat the quality of a wood-fire pizza if you've never had one. They also have a list of yummy specials outside by the entrance.
There is outside seating in addition to beers and wines on tap! Though The Beach usually closes at 3pm, you can still have a righteous happy hour on Fridays as they're open till 9pm. They offer some local beverages, vegan dessert, and great choices between salads, sandwiches, and pizzas. Don't miss this hole-in-the-wall gem located in Old Town!<//Review>

< text>
I had my 2008 F-150 serviced here. The problem was in the transmission and the recommended fix was a new transmission. This was no surprise to me since I'm very well-versed in the mechanics of vehicles and had already determined that myself. I just needed an approved shop to do the work in order for my warranty to cover the expense.

Monarch did not disappoint. I didn't lead on that I already knew what was wrong, I just let them do their thing. They did not try to lead me on at all. They communicated clearly and didn't hide any details. Any time the 'ball was in their court' during the warranty process, they worked very quickly; much faster than I anticipated. The process was effortless and painless.

If my vehicles require any work that I cannot complete myself, for whatever reason, Monarch will be my first call.

I think it goes without saying, but I will anyways, I am very VERY pleased with the customer service I received from Monarch's Service Department. Hopefully I get to purchase a vehicle from them sometime in the near future, once this truck is paid off.< /text>
